Duplicate / conflicting data

Adding the same project name twice → your schema has a PK so it'll reject it, but make sure the error message shown in the UI is clear, not a raw 500 crash
Submitting the same post (same user, platform, exact same minute) twice → your uq_post_time constraint handles this, the UI should say something readable like "This user already has a post at that time"

Missing / empty fields

Submitting a project with no name, or a post with no text → your frontend validates these, but he may try bypassing the UI entirely with curl like we did
Try this yourself: curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/posts -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{}' — make sure it returns a clean 400 error, not a crash

Invalid foreign keys

Adding an analysis result for a post ID that doesn't exist
Adding an analysis result for a project that doesn't exist
Your backend checks both of these already

Boundary values

A username longer than 40 characters
Negative likes/dislikes
An end date before the start date on a project
A post that reposts a non-existent post ID

Query edge cases

Querying posts with no filters at all (returns everything — make sure it doesn't time out)
Querying an experiment name that doesn't exist
Searching for a username that has no posts

Linking accounts

Linking the same account to two different people
Linking an account to a person ID that doesn't exist
